name: Moscow
summary: In the wake of a preordained election, Russian President Vladimir Putin asserts that the results reflect public support for his policies. Meanwhile, a concert venue near Moscow has witnessed a deadly attack by gunmen, leaving more than 60 people dead. The Islamic State has claimed responsibility for the attack, which has also resulted in over 130 injuries. As the death toll rises to 133, Putin has addressed the nation, while officials from the National Security Council have dismissed any involvement from Ukraine. The attack has prompted questions about ISIL's motives for targeting Russia. Four gunmen have been arrested in connection with the incident. The United States Department of State has condemned the terrorist attack and is closely monitoring the situation.

name: Riley Strain found
summary: The body of missing college student Riley Strain was discovered in the Cumberland River in Nashville, Tennessee. Police have ruled out foul play, but the exact cause of death remains under investigation. Strain's disappearance had sparked a search involving multiple agencies and volunteers, with his bank card found near the river earlier. The recovery of Strain's body brings closure to his family and friends, but also raises questions about the circumstances surrounding his death. Authorities continue to investigate and provide updates as more information becomes available.

summary: Various news sources have released summaries and updates on the ongoing child abuse case involving Ruby Franke and Jodi Hildebrandt. These entries, along with additional video footage, have showcased the severity of the neglect the children endured. Prosecutors emphasize religious extremism as a motive for Franke's actions, with new evidence highlighting the extent to which her husband was unaware of the abuse. name: Yale basketball
summary: In a stunning upset, the Yale Bulldogs, a 13th seed in the NCAA Tournament, defeated the fourth-seeded Auburn Tigers in the first round. The Bulldogs' victory extended their Ivy League dominance, as they have now triumphed over multiple top-ranked ACC teams in recent years. Auburn's title ambitions were dashed by Yale's tenacious defense and timely offense, which rallied from a deficit to secure a 78-76 victory. The Bulldogs' triumph was widely celebrated, marking another instance of an Ivy League team defying expectations and causing a major upset in March Madness.

summary: Zach Edey, Purdue's star center, has made significant headlines due to his towering stature and impressive performance on the court. Despite the controversy, Edey's achievements have been widely recognized, including his first 30-20 game in March Madness since 1995 and his unanimous selection to the AP All-America first team. summary: Duke University's men's basketball team is set to face the University of Vermont in the first round of the NCAA Tournament in Brooklyn, with the game being broadcast on CBS. However, slow starts have been a challenge for the Blue Devils recently. Despite this, Duke's strong shooting and physical play should help them in the second round against James Madison. Notably, Duke received the third-lowest final ranking in 17 years, which may impact their performance in the tournament.
